  "prompt": "Who discovered chloroplast?",
  "response": "Chloroplasts were formally discovered and described by the German botanist **Andreas Franz Wilhelm Schimper** in **1883**. Schimper was a pioneering figure in plant physiology and microscopy, and he introduced the term \"chloroplast\" to describe the green, photosynthetic organelles found in plant cells. His work elucidated the structure and function of chloroplasts, highlighting their critical role in the process of photosynthesis\u2014the mechanism by which plants convert light energy into chemical energy.\n\nWhile earlier scientists had observed similar structures within plant cells, it was Schimper's detailed studies and characterization that established chloroplasts as distinct and essential components of plant biology. His contributions laid the groundwork for our modern understanding of cellular organelles and the intricate processes that sustain plant life.\n\n**Key Points:**\n- **Discoverer:** Andreas Franz Wilhelm Schimper\n- **Year of Discovery:** 1883\n- **Contribution:** Coined the term \"chloroplast\" and detailed their structure and role in photosynthesis",
